  "content": "<figure>\n<blockquote cite=\"https://clarkesworldmagazine.com/kritzer_05_23/\">\n<p><em>I just miss doing art. Don’t you?</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<figcaption>\n<cite><a href=\"https://clarkesworldmagazine.com/kritzer_05_23/\">Naomi Kritzer, <em>Better Living Through Algorithms</em></a></cite>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>i bought myself some presents.</p>\n<p><img alt=\" a picture of a table with a tall jar of colored pencils and the cap laying next to it. underneath is a sketchbook, which has a drawing of the pencils themselves. inside the drawing is another sketchbook, with a tiny miniature nested pencil drawing. \" src=\"https://jyn.dev/assets/colored-pencils.webp\" /></p>\n<p>i like them. they're nice.</p>\n<p><img alt=\" a picture of a loose blank paper with a drawing of the sunset. in the distance are two mountains with an island nearby. in the midground are two sailboats. their names are just barely visible: STABERINDE and GREY MATTER. in the foreground are two people sitting on the beach on a wooden log. their footsteps trail off the page. one says to the other: &quot;do you think the sun ever thinks about us?&quot; \" src=\"https://jyn.dev/assets/sunset.webp\" /></p>"
}